
[1]roundly

   ROUND'LY, adv.

   1. In a round form or manner.

   2. Openly; boldly; without reserve; peremptorily.

   He affirms every thing roundly.

   3. Plainly; fully. He gives them roundly to understand that their duty
   is submission.

   4. Briskly; with speed.

   When the mind has brought itself to attention, it will be able to cope
   with difficulties and master them, and then it may go on roundly.

   5. Completely; to the purpose; vigorously; in earnest.
